    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "At Snowflake, we are powering the era of the agentic enterprise. To usher in this new era, we seek AI-native thinkers across every function who are energized by the opportunity to reinvent how they work. You don’t just use tools; you possess an innate curiosity, treating AI as a high-trust collaborator that is core to how you solve problems and accelerate your impact. We look for low-ego individuals who thrive in dynamic and fast-moving environments and move with an experimental mindset — who rapidly test emerging capabilities to discover simpler, more powerful ways to deliver results. At Snowflake, your role isn't just to execute a function, but to help redefine the future of how work gets done.\n\nSnowflake is a cutting-edge, global data platform that empowers thousands of organizations to effortlessly store, process, and harness the full potential of their data with unparalleled efficiency and scalability. \n\nSnowflake Migrations is the expert for migrating to the Snowflake platform, covering code conversion, data migration, data validation, data testing, reporting, and data ingestion, and creates tools like SnowConvert to accelerate the migration of legacy databases.\n\nWe're looking for a talented Senior Software Application Engineer to help us continue to grow and build new migrations tools and applications by using cutting-edge technologies.  \n\n\nAS A SENIOR SOFTWARE APPLICATION ENGINEER AT SNOWFLAKE, YOU WILL:\n\n - Innovate the next generation of migration and modernization tools.\n\n - Innovate and build highly secured and reliable software to accelerate customer workload migration.\n\n - Collaborate with engineers, product managers, solution architects, and designers to deliver cross-functional initiatives.\n\n - Ensure operational excellence, meeting reliability, availability, and performance goals.\n\n \n\n\nOUR IDEAL SENIOR SOFTWARE APPLICATION ENGINEER  WILL HAVE:\n\n - 7+ years of industry experience designing and building software solutions.\n\n - Extremely strong fundamental computer science skills.\n\n - Deep, multi-faceted appreciation in building end-to-end, customer-facing products.\n\n - Interest in establishing development processes and best practices, especially regarding quality and velocity.\n\n - Strong knowledge of C#, python, and databases.\n\n - Strong written, verbal, and technical communication skills.\n\n - BS/MS/PhD in Computer Science or related majors.\n\nEvery Snowflake employee is expected to follow the company’s confidentiality and security standards for handling sensitive data. Snowflake employees must abide by the company’s data security plan as an essential part of their duties. It is every employee's duty to keep customer information secure and confidential.\n\nSnowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.\n\nHow do you want to make your impact?\n\nFor jobs located in the United States, please visit the job posting on the Snowflake Careers Site for salary and benefits information: careers.snowflake.com http://careers.snowflake.com",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
